# Project standards

Apply to all work in this repository unless a scoped rule overrides.

## Layout

- `backend/` — NestJS + TypeORM API (layered architecture).
- `ui/` — React + Vite single-page app.
- `docker-compose.yml` brings up Postgres + backend + ui.

## Naming

- Use descriptive names. Avoid single-letter identifiers (i, j, x) except in trivial math.
- Loop indices should be readable (`index`, `ticketIndex`).
- Prefer clarity over brevity.

## Architecture

- Minimize scope: smallest correct diff; do not change unrelated code.
- Reuse existing patterns, barrel exports, and the `@/` path alias (maps to `src/`).
- Do not over-engineer abstractions for one-off use.
- Keep the in-process model intact (in-memory cache, in-process SSE bus, timer-based reaper). Do not reintroduce Redis or extra infra without being asked.

## Imports & exports

- Use barrel exports: add new public APIs to the folder's `index.ts`
  (`@/interfaces`, `@/services`, `@/entities`, `@/apis`, etc.).
- Import the `@/` alias rather than long relative paths.
- Do not import domain types from service/controller/component files — import them from the dedicated `interfaces`/`types` folders.

## API response shape

- The backend wraps every success in `{ status, statusCode, message, entity }`
  and every error in `{ status: false, statusCode, message, error }`.
- New raw/streaming endpoints (e.g. SSE) must opt out with `@SkipSuccessWrapper()`.
- The UI unwraps `entity` centrally in `@/utilities` (`unwrapApiEntity`); keep new API calls going through `apiGet`/`apiPost`.

## After writing code

- Backend: `cd backend && npm run build` and `npm test`.
- UI: `cd ui && npm run tsc` (and `npm run build` for a full check).
- Run ESLint with `--fix` on edited backend paths.
- Only create git commits when the user explicitly asks.
